\f0\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb4 Transitions in code-based video editing are essentially mathematical functions that map the 
\f4\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 current frame
\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  to a 
\f4\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 visual property
\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  (like position, scale, or blur).\cb1 \
\cb4 Since you are looking for more advanced React-based (Remotion) transitions, here are three essential patterns: the 
\f4\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 Slide
\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 , the 
\f4\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 Spring
\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 , and the 
\f4\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 Blur Dissolve
\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 .\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f4\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb4 1. The "Spring" Scale (Natural Bounce)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb4 Instead of a linear animation, a 
\f4\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 Spring
\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  uses physics to create a professional, "bouncy" feel. This is perfect for bringing in titles or icons.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs28 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf8 \cb9 \strokec8 TypeScript\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\fs21 \AppleTypeServices \cf8 \cb9 import \{ spring, useCurrentFrame, useVideoConfig \} from 'remotion';\
\
const SpringTransition = () => \{\
  const frame = useCurrentFrame();\
  const \{ fps \} = useVideoConfig();\
\
  // Create a spring value that starts at frame 0\
  const scale = spring(\{\
    frame,\
    fps,\
    config: \{\
      stiffness: 100,\
      damping: 10,\
      mass: 0.5,\
    \},\
  \});\
\
  return (\
    <div style=\{\{ transform: `scale($\{scale\})` \}\}>\
      <h1>Bouncy Title</h1>\
    </div>\
  );\
\};\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f4\b\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb4 \strokec2 2. The Directional Slide (Slide-In)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb4 This uses the 
\f6\fs28 \AppleTypeServices \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 interpolate
\f0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb4 \strokec2  function to move an element from off-screen (
\f7\i\fs38\fsmilli19360 \AppleTypeServices X
\f8\i0 =\uc0\u8722 1000
\f0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 ) to the center (
\f7\i\fs38\fsmilli19360 \AppleTypeServices X
\f8\i0 =0
\f0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 ).\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs28 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf8 \cb9 \strokec8 TypeScript\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\fs21 \AppleTypeServices \cf8 \cb9 import \{ interpolate, useCurrentFrame \} from 'remotion';\
\
const SlideIn = () => \{\
  const frame = useCurrentFrame();\
\
  // Map frames 0-20 to a horizontal position\
  const translateX = interpolate(frame, [0, 20], [-1000, 0], \{\
    extrapolateRight: 'clamp',\
  \});\
\
  return (\
    <div style=\{\{ transform: `translateX($\{translateX\}px)` \}\}>\
      <p>This slides in from the left.</p>\
    </div>\
  );\
\};\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f4\b\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb4 \strokec2 3. The Cinematic Blur Dissolve\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb4 This transition affects two layers. As the first layer fades and blurs out, the second layer fades and sharpens in.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs28 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf8 \cb9 \strokec8 TypeScript\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\fs21 \AppleTypeServices \cf8 \cb9 import \{ interpolate, useCurrentFrame \} from 'remotion';\
\
const BlurDissolve = () => \{\
  const frame = useCurrentFrame();\
  \
  // Transitions between frame 30 and 45\
  const opacity = interpolate(frame, [30, 45], [1, 0], \{ extrapolateRight: 'clamp' \});\
  const blur = interpolate(frame, [30, 45], [0, 20], \{ extrapolateRight: 'clamp' \});\
\
  return (\
    <div style=\{\{ \
      opacity, \
      filter: `blur($\{blur\}px)`,\
      position: 'absolute' \
    \}\}>\
      <img src="historical_map.jpg" alt="Map" />\
    </div>\
  );\
\};\
