\f0\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb4 To achieve a professional, multi-layered look for YouTube Shorts, you need a system that handles 
\f4\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 dynamic depth
\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  (for those clean PNG cutouts) and 
\f4\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 seamless transitions
\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  (for B-roll and stills).\cb1 \
\cb4 In the 2026 Remotion ecosystem, the most efficient way to do this is by combining 
\f6\fs28 \AppleTypeServices \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 @remotion/transitions
\f0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb4 \strokec2  for sequence-to-sequence flow and custom 
\f4\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 Parallax Components
\f0\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  for your image/PNG layers.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 \
